---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Projects">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Engineering & Infrastructure</h1>
        
        <div class="space-y-16">
            <!-- TraceIQ Project -->
            <article>
                <div class="mb-6">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 flex items-center gap-3">
                        TraceIQ Architecture
                        <span class="text-xs border border-emerald-500 text-emerald-400 px-2 py-1 rounded">Active Development</span>
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-500 font-mono text-sm">2024 - Present</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-gray-400">
                    <p>
                        TraceIQ represents the culmination of modern AI infrastructure engineering. It is a fully containerized, self-hosted intelligence stack designed to operate independently of major cloud provider lock-in while leveraging best-in-class tools.
                    </p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3 text-lg font-semibold">The Technical Stack</h3>
                    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 list-none pl-0">
                        <li class="bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded border border-gray-800">
                            <strong class="text-white block mb-1">Memory & Context</strong>
                            Mem0 (Open Source) with Qdrant Vector Store and Neo4j Graph Database for complex relationship mapping.
                        </li>
                        <li class="bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded border border-gray-800">
                            <strong class="text-white block mb-1">Compute & Inference</strong>
                            Ollama running local quantized models (Llama 3, Mistral) for privacy-preserving inference.
                        </li>
                        <li class="bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded border border-gray-800">
                            <strong class="text-white block mb-1">Orchestration</strong>
                            N8N for visual workflow automation, integrated with custom Python scripts and MCP servers.
                        </li>
                        <li class="bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded border border-gray-800">
                            <strong class="text-white block mb-1">Gateway & Security</strong>
                            Cloudflare Tunnels for zero-trust exposure, Meta MCP Gateway for tool aggregation.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </article>

            <!-- Legacy/Physical Projects -->
            <article class="border-t border-gray-800 pt-16">
                <div class="mb-6">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Physical Infrastructure & Automation</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-500 font-mono text-sm">2010 - 2023</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-gray-400">
                    <p>
                        Before the AI revolution, my focus was on the physical layer of technology. I specialized in bridging the gap between traditional electrical systems and emerging digital automation standards.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-gray-200 font-semibold">Commercial AV & Surveillance</h3>
                            <p>
                                Designed and installed complex low-voltage systems for bars, restaurants, and offices. This included structured cabling, IP camera networks, and distributed audio/video matrices controlled by early automation platforms.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-gray-200 font-semibold">The Analog-to-Digital Bridge</h3>
                            <p>
                                Working alongside traditional electricians, I facilitated the transition to IP-based systems. I brought IT network standards to the physical trade, implementing VLANs for security systems and robust Wi-Fi backbones for smart home automation.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>